President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived Gombe Township Stadium for his re-election campaign. Buhari was accompanied by Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo, and other dignitaries at exactly 11:57am. The arrival of the president was welcomed with thunderous applause from mammoth crowd that gathered at the stadium. The MC’s and officials of the All Progressives Congress (APC) are finding it difficult to control the crowds to remain quite and listen to the speeches. Details later…… Gombe to receive President Buhari campaign train on Saturday 2019 campaigns: Story behind ‘mammoth’ crowds Don’t see 2019 elections as declaration of war, Buhari urges politicians